title: Wind Solar Wind Experiment (SWE), 9 sec solar wind electron pitch-angle distribution averages - K. Ogilvie (NASA/GSFC)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/wind/swe/swe_m0/2002/wi_m0_swe_20020816_v01.cdf. The most common cadence occurred for 27.3897% of the 1788 timesteps. Cadence = 12684 [ms] = PT12.684S.
